cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the control and optimization of wireless multihop networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of distributed algorithms for solving the optimization problem, which is related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of queue length information, which is a topic in Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and the optimization problem is solved using an incremental gradient ascent algorithm, which is a topic in Machine Learning (cs.MA).
